  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Charmant Petit Lac Ecohotel Parc &amp; Spa is a modern mountain hotel, a short walk from Route Ramey, <a data-udi="umb://document/090d2ea7dadc4d03ba25ba2f7aaac686" href="/{localLink:umb://document/090d2ea7dadc4d03ba25ba2f7aaac686}" title="Champoluc">Champoluc's</a> main street. It's really convenient for accessing the slopes, with the Crest gondola about 300 metres away, your gateway to the beautiful Monterosa ski area. The hotel's classic yet modern design mixes seamlessly with the surrounding mountain landscape. The balance with nature is obvious in the details: wooden walls and soft fabrics made of natural materials provide comfort, while resources like water and electricity are generated with geothermal and solar thermal systems. </p>
<h2>Cosy Elegance</h2>
<p>The cosy interior with an open fire gives a warm ambience to come back to after a day out on the mountains. We love heading to the lounge bar area for an after-ski drink, or a digestive before heading to bed. The spacious bedrooms stand out with their fresh feel and mountain views, each of the bedrooms is furnished in a traditional yet modern Alpine style with warm wood and soft furnishings. Just imagine the sound of the Evacon River flowing past as you soak up the views from your balcony. </p>
<p>You'll soon see how every single aspect of this hotel has been carefully thought out. Built ecologically using renewable resources and sustainable materials, including locally sourced wood, the hotel blends in with the alpine landscape. The hotel is equipped with an open circuit geothermal system which, with three heat pumps, meets all the thermal needs of the building: heating, hot water, the swimming pool and spa. It also has a solar thermal system.</p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>Available on bed and breakfast, you will be well taken care of with plenty of choice from the breakfast buffet. If you are looking for somewhere for dinner, the hotel has its own gourmet restaurant and bistro so you won't have to go far for dinner either. Dining in the charming Lo Restò Tatà, you can enjoy tasty evening meals which are inspired by the Val d'Ayas, with organic, seasonal and local products used throughout the menu. Alternatively, you can head to Lo Bistrot and enjoy delicious meals during lunch and dinner - be sure to try some traditional dishes from the Aosta Valley with a glass of local wine from the cellar (pay locally).</p>
<h2>Wellness</h2>
<p>You need to make sure you spend some time in the spa, too. The adults only spa area is the perfect place to unwind after a day of exploring the Monterosa Ski Area - the sauna, steam rooms, sensory showers and whirlpools are the perfect antidote to any aches. Families can enjoy the pool area which overlooks the Monterosa, and includes a jacuzzi, hydromassage seats, waterfall and Kneipp bath.  For a little extra treat, massages and treatments are available for a local fee.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
